cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the problem of person re-identification, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel domain adaptation technique that involves unsupervised learning, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses synthetic data, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of HDR environment maps for illumination modeling could also place the paper under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, since the paper deals with surveillance cameras, it could be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics).
